The paper deals with improving the accuracy and robustness of deep neural nets, which are core topics in machine learning and computer vision. The proposed method involves replacing the output activation function of DNNs with a graph Laplacian-based high dimensional interpolating function, which integrates the advantages of both deep learning and manifold learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
